備註 Remarks
     課程要求：
學生需能融合普通心理學、統計學、與實驗法的基本知識，養成批判能力。

中文課程介紹：
    本課程強調課堂講演與從事實驗並重，安排了兩學期的教學內容。除了一般的實驗法及設計入門之訓練外，本課程之特色是企圖把實驗心理學歷史之相關重要發展串成脈絡架構，並精選一般普通心理學教本裡曾介紹過的具代表性實驗進行詳細設計操作，加深學生印象，期使心理實驗法課程內容不至於淪為隨意零散的實驗拼湊，不管是實驗的設計進行或後續的資料分析，除了讓同學瞭解過去實驗心理學進行實驗的方式以外，也都企圖反映研究水準最近的發展，包括現代化電腦科技的程序控制與資料分析技術。學生無須具備複雜電腦知識，只要花極短時間學會用電腦文書處理程式，即可勝任本課。雖非重點，但有興趣的學生也可以在本課裡額外學到設計複雜心理實驗電腦程式的入門技巧。各種反映最新發展的教材及摘要於課前張貼於網頁或隨堂發放。上學期的教學強調傳統實驗法的內容，並由淺入深，慢慢帶領學生接觸電腦，至下學期則正式有系統讓學生瞭解電腦在現代實驗心理學裡扮演的角色。所有提供讓學生進行實習的實驗都是實驗室研究規格的實驗，不僅僅只是一般心理實驗法教材裡的小規模展示用實驗而已，很多實驗的設計更規劃成某些經典論文實驗的複製甚至修改，期使學生能實際面對真正研究格局的實驗並操作其後的資料分析過程。透過這樣的安排，希望學生可以融合實驗心理學歷史觀、現代統計學、與現代心理學實驗設計與技術於一爐。並且，所有實驗的設計，都特別強調實驗背後的理論基礎、變項的挑選與混淆變項的處理，不僅僅只是讓學生實驗操作與資料分析而已。

英文課程介紹 (English Course Introduction)：
    This is a two-semester course. Both lecture and experimentation will be equally emphasized. In the first three months, issues of how to make strict causal inference in behavioral science will be described in detail. And then, different domains of methodological development, supplemented with example experiments, will be conceptually linked together to provide a thorough understanding of the history of experimental psychology. From the beginning of the second semester on, recently developing modern techniques and skills about computerized psychological experiments will be gradually introduced. At the last two months, replication studies of well established paradigms of cognitive experiment will be illustrated and be conducted by students. All the experiments assigned to be practiced are not just for demonstration but are as scale as real research experiments instead. This allows students to modify the default experimental design and easily manipulate the additional independent variables interested. There is no pre-requisite programming skills necessary for students to acquire the concept of doing computerized psychological experiments in this course. Students would at last learn about the experimental methodology, including concepts of basic factorial experimental designs, and important historical developments of experimental psychology, including conducting experiments of traditional psychophysics and modern cognitive psychology. They would also be acquainted with the basic concepts of organizing experiments, teasing apart confounding variables, and handling data analyses via modern computer techniques. Courses of introductory psychology and statistics are pre-required.

 




